						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Śingāravallabhasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1322, Vikrama, Mārgaśira, ba. 7, Wednesday, corresponding to 1400 A.D., December 8.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift a pillar to the temple of Śriṅgārarāya by Tammi-Śeṭṭi, son of Aḍapa Allāḍi-Śeṭṭi of Penugoṇḍa.</p>						

